problem:
We say that A⊂ ℕ has the translation property if, for every n, there exists some integer t_n≥ 1 such that, for all 1≤ a≤ n,a∈ A\quad\textrm{ if and only if }\quad a+t_n∈ A.{UL}
{LI}Does the set of the sums of two squares have the translation property?{/LI}
{LI}If we partition all primes into P\sqcup Q, such that each set contains \gg x/\log x many primes ≤ x for all large x, then can the set of integers only divisible by primes from P have the translation property?{/LI}
{LI}If A is the set of squarefree numbers then how fast does the minimal such t_n grow? Is it true that t_n>\exp(n^c) for some constant c>0?{/LI}
{/UL}

